Meztli Matadamas

Bio

I am a mexican researcher with expertise on systems biology and bioinformatics applied to the study of human diseases, such as cancer. My research is focused on multi-omics data to find potential biomarkers and therapeutic targets. My studies were held at UNAM, but now I have been selected to perform a postdoctoral position at University of Luxembourg.

Education

Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México | Mexico city, Mexico

Ph.D. in Biomedical Sciences | January 2016 - June 2021

Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México | Mexico city, Mexico

B.S. in Genomic Sciences | August 2010 - September 2014

Experience

Novartis | Next Generation Scientist Program | June 2019 - August 2019

Baylor College of Medicine | Project Intern | August 2013 - July 2014
